'''Suwa Shrine''' (諏訪神社, すわじんじゃ) is a Shinto shrine located in {{ill|Kanagawa Prefecture|ja|神奈川県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Fujisawa City|ja|藤沢市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Katase. It is also known as Katase Suwa Shrine (片瀬諏訪神社). The shrine is divided into two sections: the western Shimosha (lower shrine) and the eastern Kamisha (upper shrine).

== Deities ==
* {{ill|Takeminakata-no-Mikoto|ja|建御名方命|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Takeminakata-no-Mikoto)
* {{ill|Yasakatotome-no-Mikoto|ja|八坂刀売命|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Yasakatotome-no-Mikoto)

== History ==
The shrine was founded in the 7th year of {{ill|Yōrō|ja|養老|qq=draft|qq=draft}} ({{ill|723 AD|ja|723rd year|qq=draft|qq=draft}}). It enshrines the divine spirit of {{ill|Suwa Taisha|ja|諏訪大社|1=Suwa-taisha|qq=draft|qq=draft}} of {{ill|Shinano Province|ja|信濃国|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, making it the oldest among those that received a portion of the spirit (御分霊) sent to other regions. The Shimosha was relocated from Miyabata in 812 AD (the 3rd year of {{ill|Kōnin|ja|弘仁|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), to a lakeside location with whale bones, while the Kamisha was relocated in 826 AD (the 3rd year of {{ill|Tenchō|ja|天長|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) from Suwa Gayatani to the mountainside of Nami-ai. In 1873 (Meiji 6), the shrine was designated as a village shrine. The shrine building of the Shimosha was rebuilt in 1941 (Showa 16), along with a new administrative office. Additionally, the one-bay shrine ({{ill|Ryū-zukuri|ja|流造|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) at the Kamisha was completed as part of the 60th Anniversary Celebration of the reign of the {{ill|Showa Emperor|ja|昭和天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.<ref name="jinjyacho-katasesuwa">[http://www.kanagawa-jinja.or.jp/search_dtl.php4?jid=535&cd=1206019&scd=&npg=0 Suwa Shrine] (Kanagawa Prefecture Shrine Agency)</ref>

In Reiwa 5 (2023), the shrine celebrated 1300 years since its establishment, with a 1300th Anniversary Celebration held on October 22.

== Annual Festivals ==
* New Year's Festival (元旦祭): January 1
* Tanabata Festival: Mid-June to July 7
* Summer Grand Festival:
** August 23: Banner Raising, Procession of the Sacred Object, Temporary Palace Wearing Ritual, and commencement announcement for the Upper Suwa Shrine Festival
** August 26: Evening Palace Ceremony
** August 27: Beach Descent Ceremony, Festival (unspecified), and Divine Blessing Festival
** August 28: Return Procession and conclusion announcement for the Upper Suwa Shrine Festival
* Niiname-sai (新嘗祭): Late November (on Sunday)
* Great Purification Ritual (大祓): December 31

== Local Information ==
; Address:
* {{ill|Osaka Prefecture|ja|大阪府|qq=draft|qq=draft}} {{ill|Fujisawa City|ja|藤沢市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Katase 2-chōme, 21-16
; Transportation:
* Nearest Station: {{ill|Kintetsu South Osaka Line|ja|近鉄南大阪線|qq=draft|qq=draft}}{{ill|Fujisawa Station|ja|藤沢駅|qq=draft|qq=draft}}; approximately an 8‑minute walk (about 600 m to the southeast).

